OL,6,F"The BBC is operationally and
OL,7,Feditorially independent, but given the
OL,8,Fincredibly serious nature of this
OL,9,Fissue, the Secretary of State has
OL,10,Fspoken to the BBC to raise concerns on
OL,11,Fa number of points regarding the
OL,12,Fhandling of their own investigations
OL,13,Finto Huw Edwards, what safeguards and
OL,14,Fprocesses had been followed in this
OL,15,Fcase, and additionally, what further
OL,16,Faction may be taken, especially with
OL,17,Fregard to the handling of licence fee
OL,18,Fpayers' money."
